PNOF5 coefficients C^J and C^K that multiply J and K integrals

    E = 2\sum_p n_pH_p + \sum_{pq} C^J_{pq}J_{qp} - \sum_{pq} C^K_{pq}K_{qp}

    C^J_{pq} =  egin{cases}
                 2 n_p n_q & if p \in \Omega_g, q \in \Omega_f,  g 
eq g\
                 0         & otherwise
               \end{cases}

    C^K_{pq} =  egin{cases}
                 n_p n_q        & if p \in \Omega_g, q \in \Omega_f,  g 
eq g\
                 \sqrt{n_p n_q} & if p,q \in \Omega_g ( (p \leq F, q > F) or (p > F, q \leq F) )\
                -\sqrt{n_p n_q} & if p 
eq q \in \Omega_g p,q > F \
                 0              & otherwise
               \end{cases}
